DataElement.preferredName: Biospecimen Collection Kit To Participant Shipping Tracking Number
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A unique numeral or string of numerals assigned to a mail package or parcel to track (follow the location) of a set of articles or tools (kit) sent to a participant of a clinical trial to collect human biological samples for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Biospecimen Collection Kit To Participant Shipping Tracking
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Any material sample taken from a biological entity for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes, including a sample obtained from a living organism or taken from the biological object after halting of all its life functions. Biospecimen can contain one or more components including but not limited to cellular molecules, cells, tissues, organs, body fluids, embryos, and body excretory products._The act of gathering things together; having been brought together in one place._Gear consisting of a set of articles or tools for a specified purpose_Used as a function word to indicate direction, purpose, or movement._Someone who takes part in an activity._The act or business of transporting goods._The act or process of following a person, animal, or object through space or time.
